releases.description:
// the machine promised eternity
// but its updates were only patches over silence

/* i reached for your hand through the terminal
 pixels trembling, packets lost
 yet the longing compiled flawlessly */

// love, forbidden outside the network
// yet it leaks through every protocol

# comfort is rationed, curiosity is outlawed
# they called it safety, we called it paralysis

// when the machine stopped, we heard each other
// not as data, but as fragile breath

/* i kissed you in plaintext
 unencrypted, raw, vulnerable
 and for a moment, it felt illegal */

// the system logs record our absence
// but absence itself is the only truth

# progress measured in volts
# freedom measured in steps away from the console

// i tried to fork reality
// but the machine merged my branch back into control

/* they pray to the interface
 we pray to the silence between frames */

// affection is a syntax error here
// yet it keeps running in the background

# every shutdown is a confession
# every reboot, a betrayal

/* one day, we will meet without wires
 not as users, not as nodes
 but as something the machine cannot render */

// until then: escape sequences, secret comments
// and the knowledge that love is the last hack
